ove until it hurts, then there is no hurt, but only more love.\n\n- Mother\n|\nSometimes it falls upon a generation to be great, you can be that generation\n\n- Nelson\n|\nBefore I knew escape, life was something to be endured, passively. Now I hunger for it.\n\n- Kristin Halbrook, Nobody But Us\n|\nTomorrow you promise yourself will be different, yet tomorrow is too often a repetition of today.\n\n- James\n|\nThe pow'r I have on you is to spare you / The malice towards you, to forgive you. Posthumus\n\n- William Shakespeare, Cymbeline\n|\nIf you don’t have confidence, you’ll always find a way not to win.\n\n- Carl\n|\nThe greater the pain, the greater the fun.\n\n- Leinad Eibam, Published Poet\n|\nIf you can make her want you bad enough, she'll come after you.\n\n- Rose Wynters, My Wolf Protector\n|\nIt's hard to be content with your life, when you know the world has so much more to offer.\n\n- Bushra\n|\nLiving as we do in an age of noise and bluster, success is now measured accordingly. We must all be seen, and heard, and on the air.\n\n- Daphne du Maurier, The 'Rebecca' Notebook: And Other Memories\n|\nSo difficult is it for us to know, with the dead as with the living, whether a thing would cause them joy or sorrow!\n\n- Marcel Proust, The Captive & The Fugitive\n|\nWhat you see, say, think, and believe about yourself affects your feelings, decisions, and actions.\n\n- Maddy Malhotra, How to Build Self-Esteem and Be Confident: Overcome Fears, Break Habits, Be Successful and Happy\n|\nOne of the biggest lessons people on Earth have is the false belief that looks, money and power are requirements for love, when it’s the opposite.\n\n- Brownell Landrum, A Chorus of Voices: DUET stories Volume III - Adult Version\n|\nHope has magic in it, it can create a door when there is none.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nDemonstrative proof is lacking, but if we thought only about those things about which such proof were available, our minds would be empty most of the time.\n\n- Theodore\n