ow to read and refusing to learn.\n\n- Patricia\n|\nLife cannot be lived without irritations and angers; fights and placation-A cycle of Karma, wheels of succor.\n\n- Aporva Kala, Life... Love... Kumbh...\n|\nIf you're able to help some people and make them smile and make them realize that life is good, then that's worth so much more than buying a pair of shoes.\n\n- Maria\n|\nBelieve in you because you are powerful.Ana Maria Frith, Limitless Change Your Life\n\n- Ana\n|\nNot only is love blind, it’s a little hard of hearing.\n\n- Brian P. Cleary, You Oughta Know By Now\n|\nThe physical world exists, but that’s only the paint and canvas; that’s only the instrument we use to make music; that’s only the stage where the play is performed.\n\n- Dennis Vickers, Mikawadizi Storms\n|\nToday we fight. Tomorrow we fight. The day after, we fight. And if this disease plans on whipping us, it better bring a lunch, 'cause it's gonna have a long day doing it.\n\n- Jim Beaver, Life's That Way\n|\nRelief is a wonderful emotion, highly underrated. In fact, I prefer it to elation or joy. Relief lets the air out of the Tire of Pain.\n\n- Adriana Trigiani, Rococo\n|\nWe are, or rather our natural desire to evade pain and to attain pleasure is, the primary reason we do or say every single thing we do or say.\n\n- Mokokoma Mokhonoana, The Selfish Genie: A Satirical Essay on Altruism\n|\nIn the midst of our struggle to find out who we are, there are infinite possibilities for beauty, and hope, and wonder, and love.\n\n- Mandy Hale, The Single Woman: Life, Love, and a Dash of Sass\n|\nThis is the day the Lord has made, suck it up and rejoice.\n\n- Donna White Glaser, The Enemy We Know\n|\nDoing, in a life of balance, should be driven from who you have decided to be.\n\n- Patrick Rhone, Keeping It Straight: You, Me & Everything Else\n|\nYour chronological age makes you older, grownNess is a state of mind!\n\n- Sheila\n|\nTell me, who have never be knocked down by life’s circumstances? It takes grace and enough strength, to get up and begin again\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nIf you believe in “luck”, always let it be good luck. Always choose to be 'lucky', rather than 'luckless'.Be 'happy', rather than 'hapless'.\n\n- Donald L. Hicks, Look into the stillness\n|\nThe most influential and frequent voice you hear is your inner-voice. It can work in your favor or against you, depending on what you listen to and act upon.\n\n- Maddy Malhotra, How to Build Self-Esteem and Be Confident: Overcome Fears, Break Habits, Be Successful and Happy\n|\nHey Jude, don't make it bad, take a sad song and make it better.\n\n- The\n|\nIf it´s cold and cloudy outside,And you want to be a great fella,Make all your troubles go glideOpening a smile as your umbrella.\n\n- Ana Claudia Antunes, The DAO (Dancing As One) Workbook Illustrated\n|\nThat didn't happen, of course. Things never happenedlike I imagined them.\n\n- John Green, Looking for Alaska\n|\nListen, we got two stiffs and a river of red in a villa in Herne Bay...\n\n- Rhys Chamberlain, Emotion\n|\nAs there is no joy for the broken heart, there is not also an harmony to a guitar with broken strings!\n\n- Bruce\n|\nYou are here to feel the joy of life by empowering, enabling, enlightening humanity so that humanity may find its own joy.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nfor PEOPLE to rule themselves in a REPUBLIC , they must have virtue;for a TYRANT to rule in a TYRANNY ,he must use FEAR.\n\n- William J. Federer, Change to Chains-The 6,000 Year Quest for Control -Volume I-Rise of the Republic\n|\nYou hold one feather tightly in your hand, close your eyes and concentrate. The location of the other feather will appear in your mind and the magic will take you there.\n\n- Louise Courey Nadeau, Magelica's Voyage\n|\nI’m taking the leap, I’m learning to fly.\n\n- Nihar Sharma, Hijacked!\n|\nThey really hate you, yes they do. They hate everyone, how 'bout you?\n\n- Kami Garcia, Beautiful Creatures\n|\nCuriosity – if not 